
[1]proviso

   PROVI'SO, n. s as z. [L. provisus, ablative proviso, it being
   provided.] An article or clause in any statute, agreement, contract,
   grant or other writing, by which a condition is introduced; a
   conditional stipulation that affects an agreement, contract, law,
   grant, &c. The charter of the bank contains a proviso that the
   legislature may repeal it at their pleasure.
